bio.experienceSummary:
Every job I've had in life has revolved around helping children. From music lessons to college programs helping kids with special needs, I've always found joy in helping kids grow into the best versions of themselves!
I'm an Aunt to 3 and nothing makes me happier than spending time with my nieces and nephew. I grew up in a large family so I grew up babysitting. I later worked in schools teacher general music/theory, chorus and later private music lessons. Additionally, I created a non-profit to help fund teens college education.

With 20 years of experience in providing compassionate, responsible, and reliable childcare, I offer a safe and nurturing environment for children of all ages. My extensive experience includes caring for infants, toddlers, and school-aged children, as well as helping with homework, organizing activities, and managing daily routines. I am skilled in creating age-appropriate fun and educational activities while ensuring a calm, supportive atmosphere.

As a dedicated caregiver, I am focused on building trust with both parents and children, and I always prioritize safety, communication, and positive reinforcement. Whether you need a regular babysitter or occasional help, I am committed to offering peace of mind and high-quality care for your little ones.

with extensive experience caring for children of all ages, from babies to older kids. I'm very inventive and love coming up with educational activities, such as arts and crafts, to keep children engaged and support their development. I have experience looking after babies as young as 3 months and always ensure they are in a safe and caring environment. I'm patient, attentive, and enjoy using music and imaginative play to calm and entertain children. I'm also very hands-on and enjoy keeping kids active with outdoor play or trips around the city. I'm an experienced swimmer with water safety training and comfortable with pets. I collaborate closely with parents to make sure their children's needs are met and that they feel comfortable and happy. I'm CPR certified and truly enjoy taking care of children.
I have experience with autistic spectrum, both in helping the child to develop and accompanying them in therapies and activities.
I am looking for 3x a week and also work ocasional jobs

description.originalText: When I travel to New York for work or vacations, I always rely on Maria to take care of my kids. She's wonderful with them! My son, who is now 3 years old, adores her – she’s been looking after him since he was just 6 months old. My older daughter also loves Maria; she thinks she's so funny! Although they don’t see each other often because I only travel to New York occasionally, Maria is always a reliable and trustworthy person to leave the kids with when I’m away. It’s such a relief knowing they’re in good hands. I highly recommend her!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi there! I'm Alex, 29-year-old . A little about me. While theatre and the arts are my first love, I also have a passion for people. I have nannied for several families over the years, and have experience caring for children of all ages. I still keep in touch with all of the families I have worked with, they have become a part of my life and like family! I would describe myself as a compassionate, trustworthy, and fun individual. I like to make learning fun and think that creativity is very important for both children and adults alike! I look forward to hearing from you!

Hello and welcome to my Care profile! I am based on the UWS and work as an as -needed nanny for a wonderful family with three children and am looking to add to my schedule. I have a background in dance and teach dance to preschool age children. I am child and infant CPR and First Aid certified through the American Red Cross. I am a huge animal lover and have pet sitting experience. I am a graduate of Hunter College with a BA and honors in anthropology. I would love to get to know your child! Please don't hesitate to reach out with any questions.

My name is Isabel. I am a 26-year-old middle school social worker and yoga instructor. I am extremely passionate about working with children and adolescents. I am committed to providing a safe and fun space to support healthy growth and development. I began my career in residential foster care before moving into a school setting starting in 2021 which has granted me with an amazing summer break. I want to ensure that I am remaining proactive and energetic in my everyday schedule which is why I am looking for a summer job. I have two young sisters ages 12 and 9 that I consistently babysat for throughout high school and college. During this time, I also volunteered at Camp ANCHOR which is a camp that provides recreational and social opportunities for individuals with developmental and physical disabilities. I then went on to graduate with my BSW from WCU in 2018 and my MSW from NYU in 2019. All of this experience and education has equipped me with the tools needed for this position.

description.displayText: Can't say enough great things about her. I don't want to write this review to keep her as our secret ha-ha. She is an amazing sitter, great with kids ,very punctual. Thanks for a great summer !

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello family! My name is Maria. Known as Malu, and I'm from Brazil.

I describe myself as an energetic, flexible, patient, and communicative person and I love to dig through the kid's imagination and create an environment where we can have fun and discover new things together.

I started working with kids back in my home country, where I babysat two babies, worked at kids' birthday parties developing games and activities and later I also worked as a full-time nanny for a 3-year-old for over a year. After this experience, I moved to America and worked as an au pair for over a year taking care of a 6-month-old baby and a 2-and-a-half-year-old. I'm glad to say I'm still in touch with the family, and I still travel sometimes to take care of their children. 

I would love to connect and see if I can be a good fit for your family!

description.originalText:
I hired Maria to babysit my two boys (18mo and 6yo). She was absolutely amazing with both of them. My oldest kept saying how much fun he had with her. She got here early to learn about the kids and didn’t rush out the door once I got back, like many babysitters do. 
We got to know each other and we now will be hiring her on a weekly basis. I highly recommend her if you need a punctual, flexible, responsible and very kind babysitter.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello beautiful families! I am an experienced nanny and former singing teacher to young kids looking to give a helping hand out to a loving family! I am a student so I do not have much flexibility with hours, but am super responsible, dedicated and kind! I am a singer, actress and dancer so I love to engage with kids through artistic activities.
I have experience with kids all ages! Infant qualified, CPR and First aid trained.
Fluent in Spanish and English. Pet friendly! I also have a drivers license with tons of experience driving. Non smoker.
Can help with light house chores/meal prep/laundry/run errands.
Activities I enjoy doing with children:
Cooking, Baking, Singing (singing baby to sleep) Dancing, Arts and crafts, Chatting about their day, Play dates, Spending time outside (walk/stroller) Teaching Spanish, Helping out with homework Dressing up/costumes, teaching values, manners and life skills 
Can potty train
Looking forward to meeting u!

description.originalText: Great help! My first grader had trouble reading and spelling and Micaela was always eager to help. Now she reads more fluently and can spell so fast I’m so proud. My girl adores her, they loved baking brownies after school homework was done!

bio.experienceSummary:
As a nurturing and experienced childcare provider with over 16 years of experience, I'm passionate about fostering children's growth and development. My previous babysitting roles have allowed me to gain valuable experience in providing reliable childcare and supporting families.

I pride myself on being patient, calm, and creative, always striving to provide a safe and nurturing environment for children. I believe in open communication with parents and regularly update them about their child's day or any issues that arise.

I have a graduate degree and have completed coursework in early child development. I'm also certified in First Aid and CPR, ensuring that I can handle any situation that may arise. I'm fluent in Arabic, English, and French, and I'm willing to assist with travel.

My approach to childcare is centered around providing a fun and educational experience for children. I love playing outdoor sports, board games, and educational games that promote learning.

description.originalText: We couldn’t be more thrilled with the care our babysitter, [AICHS], has provided for our family. She is incredibly responsible, always punctual, and has a special way of making our BABY feel happy and engaged. Whether she’s organizing creative activities or simply reading bedtime stories, MY BABY always excited for her visits.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! My name is Wynee (like Winnie the Pooh). I'm a 30-year-old fun, responsible, and loving individual with a passion for working with children.
As an older sister, I gained valuable experience caring for my siblings. I've also worked as a counselor for a summer youth program at a daycare, caring for children from newborns to 5 years old. Additionally, I've worked with children ages 5-18 and assisted my aunt with her three children.
Previously, I worked as a paraprofessional for the Department of Education, supporting children with autism and other special needs. I'm now seeking a full-time position that allows for a more personalized, one-on-one experience with children. I firmly believe that trust and communication are essential in any childcare setting. I'm fluent in Spanish and excited to bring my skills and experience to a new role. Currently, I'm working as a part-time nanny and looking forward to finding a full-time position that lets me make a meaningful impact on lives.

description.displayText: She has excellent energy and a natural ability with kids, don't let her small stature fool you.  My son who is two listened to her !  She is playful and is willing to help out the household in addition to caring for your children.
